-judge-threatens-imprisonment-for-gag-violation-2023-10%5C%22%3Edangled%20the%20threat%20of%20%26quot%3Bimprisonment%26quot%3B%20earlier%20in%20the%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0after%20learning%20that%20Trump%20had%20violated%20his%20order%20not%20to%20disparage%20court%20staff%2C%20he%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20fine%20the%20former%20president%20%245%2C000%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20defendant's%20position%20that%20the%20violation%20was%20inadvertent%2C%20and%20given%20that%20it%20is%20a%20first%20time%20violation%2C%20this%20Court%20will%20impose%20a%20nominal%20fine%2C%20%245%2C000%2C%20payable%20to%20the%20New%20York%20Lawyers'%20Fund%20for%20Client%20Protection%2C%20within%20ten%20(10)%20days%20of%20this%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20Engoron%20wrote%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24073851-nyag-v-trump-engoron-gag-order-violation-ruling-20231020%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20sternly-worded%20ruling%20issued%20on%20Friday%20afternoon%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMake%20no%20mistake%3A%20future%20violations%2C%20whether%20intentional%20or%20unintentional%2C%20will%20subject%20the%20violator%20to%20far%20more%20severe%20sanctions%2C%20which%20may%20include%2C%20but%20are%20not%20limited%20to%2C%20steeper%20financial%20penalties%2C%20holding%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20contempt%20of%20court%2C%20and%20possibly%20imprisoning%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fine%20is%20Trump's%20penalty%20for%20violating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-trial-judge-issued-gag-order-over-attacks-on-clerk-2023-10%5C%22%3Ean%20October%203%20gag%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20banning%20him%20from%20attacks%20on%20the%20judge's%20legal%20staff%20online%20or%20in%20spoken%20statements.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gag%20was%20prompted%20by%20a%20statement%20Trump%20had%20posted%20to%20his%20Truth%20Social%20account%20earlier%20that%20day.%20The%20post%20falsely%20claimed%20that%20Engoron's%20principal%20law%20clerk%2C%20Allison%20Greenfield%2C%20was%20the%20girlfriend%20of%20New%20York%20Sen.%20Chuck%20Schumer%2C%20a%20Democrat%20frequently%20targeted%20by%20Trump%20and%20the%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%2C%20which%20identified%20the%20law%20clerk%20by%20name%2C%20photo%2C%20and%20social%20media%20link%2C%20called%20the%20fictitious%20relationship%20%26quot%3Bdisgraceful!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20when%20the%20gag%20was%20issued%2C%20Engoron%20ordered%20Trump%20to%20immediately%20remove%20the%20post%20from%20his%20Truth%20Social%20account%20and%20threatened%20serious%20sanctions%20if%20he%20persisted%20in%20such%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20%26quot%3BSchumer's%20girlfriend%26quot%3B%20post%20was%20nonetheless%20automatically%20loaded%20onto%20the%20former%20president's%20campaign%20website%2C%20where%20it%20remained%20for%20more%20than%20two%20weeks%2C%20until%20Thursday%20night%2C%20when%20the%20court%20informed%20Trump's%20lawyers%20that%20it%20was%20still%20accessible%20online%20and%20it%20was%20removed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron%2C%20who%20has%20typically%20been%20an%20affable%20presence%20on%20the%20bench%20during%20the%20trial's%20three%20weeks%2C%20reacted%20with%20notable%20anger%20when%20threatening%20Trump's%20side%20with%20sanctions%20Friday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20who%20has%20attended%20the%20trial%20sporadically%2C%20was%20not%20in%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20judge%20asked%20Trump's%20attorneys%20%26quot%3Bwhy%20this%20blatant%20violation%20of%20the%20gag%20order%20should%20not%20result%20in%20serious%20financial%20penalties%20holding%20the%20defendant%20in%20contempt%20and%20possible%20imprisonment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20attorney%20Christopher%20Kise%20called%20the%20Truth%20Social%20post's%20automatic%20appearance%20on%20the%20campaign%20site%2C%20and%20the%20campaign%20staff's%20failure%20to%20remove%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Btruly%20inadvertent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKise%20later%20supplied%20the%20judge%20with%20audience%20metrics%20showing%20that%20the%20post%20had%20only%20received%203%2C701%20unique%20page%20views%20in%20the%20two%20weeks%20it%20was%20on%20the%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-jail-trump-ny-gag-violation-judge-sets-xxxxx-fine-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697830687000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6532c65896908fd7cdb42413%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-jail-trump-ny-gag-violation-judge-sets-xxxxx-fine-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Judge%20Arthur%20Engoron%20had%20threatened%20Trump%20with%20%26quot%3Bpossible%20imprisonment%26quot%3B%20for%20violating%20his%20gag%20barring%20attacks%20on%20court%20staff.%20Instead%2C%20he'll%20pay%20a%20%245%2C000%20fine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22litaliano%40insider.com%20(Laura%20Italiano)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-jail-trump-ny-gag-violation-judge-sets-xxxxx-fine-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Put%20a%20total%20stop%20to%20manual%20scavenging%3A%20Supreme%20court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697830333000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104593099%2Cimgsize-67674.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fput-a-total-stop-to-manual-scavenging-supreme-court%2Farticleshow%2F104592981.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20passed%20a%20slew%20of%20directions%20to%20the%20Centre%20and%20states%20to%20completely%20eradicate%20manual%20scavenging%20while%20also%20asking%20for%20enhanced%20compensation%20in%20case%20of%20death%20or%20injury.%20%E2%80%8B%E2%80%8BIt%20asked%20the