%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.litprom.de%2Fen%2Fbest-books%2Fliberaturpreis%2Fthe-winner-2023%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520LiBeraturpreis%25202023%26amp%3Btext%3DPalestinian%2520author%2520Adania%2520Shibli%2520receives%2COrth%252C%2520published%2520by%2520Berenberg%2520Verlag.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2023%20LiBeraturpreis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20same%20book%2C%20published%20in%20German%20as%C2%A0%3Ci%3EEine%20Nebensache%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(Berenberg%20Verlag%2C%20translated%20by%20G%C3%BCnther%20Orth)%20at%20the%202023%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%20which%20begins%20next%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.litprom.de%2Fen%2F%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20by%20organisers%20of%20the%20prize%2C%20Litprom%2C%20which%20is%20funded%20in%20part%20by%20the%20German%20government%20and%20the%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%20said%20on%20October%2013%20that%20she%20would%20no%20longer%20receive%20the%20prize%20during%20the%20book%20fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%C2%A0a%20public%20discussion%20with%20Shibli%20and%20her%20translator%20G%C3%BCnther%20Orth%20at%20the%20book%20fair%20has%20also%20been%20cancelled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20statement%20by%20Litprom%20wrongly%20claimed%20that%20Shibli%20was%20consulted%20before%20the%20decision.%20However%2C%20Shibli%20said%20it%20was%20not%20discussed%20with%20her%20before%20the%20release%20of%20the%20statement%2C%20but%20was%20only%20presented%20to%20her%20after%20the%20decision%20had%20already%20been%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20of%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%20which%20funds%20Litprom%2C%20also%20said%20it%20stands%20in%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCyV_bnoouAw%2F%5C%22%3Ecomplete%20solidarity%20on%20the%20side%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20they%20wanted%20to%20make%20Jewish%20and%20Israeli%20voices%20%E2%80%9Cespecially%20visible%20at%20the%20fair%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20also%20condemned%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ffreedom_theatre%2Fstatus%2F1712440518880153934%2Fphoto%2F1%5C%22%3Ecancellation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20play%20of%20Hassan%20Abdulrazzak%20%E2%80%98And%20Here%20I%20Am%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20mayor%20of%20%3Cspan%3EChoisy-le-Roi%2C%20a%20commune%20in%20France.%20Abdulrazzak%E2%80%99s%20play%20is%20around%20the%20coming-of-age%20story%20of%20actor-director%20Ahmed%20Tobasi%2C%20born%20in%20Jenin%20during%20the%20first%20intifada%20of%20Palestine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20launch%20of%20%3Cem%3EA%20Day%20in%20the%20Life%20of%20Abed%20Salama%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Nathan%20Thrall%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20was%20cancelled%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20concerns%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20of%20support%20was%20signed%20by%2C%20among%20others%2C%20Nobel%20Prize%20laureates%20Abdulrazak%20Gurnah%2C%20Annie%20Ernaux%2C%20and%20Olga%20Tokarczuk%3B%20Booker%20Prize%20winners%20Anne%20Enright%2C%20Richard%20Flanagan%2C%20and%20Ian%20McEwan%3B%202021%20winner%20of%20the%20Litprom%20prize%20Pilar%20Quintana%20and%202015%20winner%20Madeleine%20Thien%3B%20dozens%20of%20publishers%20and%20literary%20agents%3B%20as%20well%20as%20many%20concerned%20writers%20from%20around%20the%20globe.%20There%20are%20now%20more%20than%201%2C300%20signatories%2C%20ArabLit%20said%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20the%20letter%20of%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20shocking%20and%20tragic%20events%20that%20began%20on%20October%207th%20and%20are%20ongoing%20today%20have%20had%20repercussions%20all%20over%20the%20globe%2C%20including%20within%20the%20publishing%20world.%20Award-winning%20Palestinian%20author%20Adania%20Shibli%2C%20who%20was%20a%20finalist%20for%20the%202020%20National%20Book%20Award%20for%20her%20book%C2%A0%3Ci%3EMinor%20Detail%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(New%20Directions%2FFitzcarraldo%2C%20translated%20by%20Elisabeth%20Jaquette)%2C%20was%20to%20receive%20Germany%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.litprom.de%2Fen%2Fbest-books%2Fliberaturpreis%2Fthe-winner-2023%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520LiBeraturpreis%25202023%26amp%3Btext%3DPalestinian%2520author%2520Adania%2520Shibli%2520receives%2COrth%252C%2520published%2520by%2520Berenberg%2520Verlag.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2023%20LiBeraturpreis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20same%20book%2C%20published%20in%20German%20as%C2%A0%3Ci%3EEine%20Nebensache%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(Berenberg%20Verlag%2C%20translated%20by%20G%C3%BCnther%20Orth)%20at%20the%202023%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%20which%20begins%20next%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2013%2C%20the%20organizers%20of%20the%20prize%2C%20Litprom%2C%20which%20is%20funded%20in%20part%20by%20the%20German%20government%20and%20the%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.litprom.de%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereleased%20a%20statement%20saying%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Shibli%20would%20no%20longer%20receive%20the%20prize%20during%20the%20book%20fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20a%20public%20discussion%20with%20Adania%20Shibli%20and%20her%20translator%20G%C3%BCnther%20Orth%20at%20the%20book%20fair%20has%20also%20been%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20originally%20said%20that%20this%20decision%20had%20been%20made%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20author%2C%20which%20was%20then%20relayed%2C%20without%20verification%2C%20by%20an%20article%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fbooks%2Ffrankfurt-book-fair-cancels-award-adania-shibli.html%3Funlocked_article_code%3Dod51UV2wwU5LpwBzcCN5WjlbZ9MVwjVX7RjEuujfuCZGcwCdT522_QHNlGtz6lIds9cZyKEJ-cp5J_G3htLwXhM_pZ4L