id%2C%20referring%20to%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20state-funded%20rogue%20private%20army%2C%20indicated%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20internal%20weakness%20and%20was%20indicative%20of%20what%20(adversity)%20may%20lie%20in%20store%20for%20its%20future%2C%20though%20he%20declined%20to%20elaborate%20on%20this%20point.%20The%20CDS%20further%20declared%20that%2C%20conversely%2C%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20economic%20heft%20was%20now%20visible%20in%20the%20political%2C%20diplomatic%20and%20military%20domains%20and%20that%20the%20world%20would%20now%20see%20a%20more%20assertive%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Chauhan%E2%80%99s%20pessimistic%20and%20somewhat%20cynical%20public%20assessment%20regarding%20the%20future%20potential%20of%20a%20vital%20Indian%20ally%20and%20provider%20of%C2%A0%2045%25%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20defence%20equipment%20and%20over%2040%25%20of%20its%20oil%20imports%2C%20have%20been%20unfavourably%20received%20in%20official%20and%20diplomatic%20circles.%20Some%20media%20reports%20have%20asserted%20that%20this%20grouping%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20military%20personnel%20should%20not%20publicly%20make%20%E2%80%98inappropriate%E2%80%99%20statements%20and%20should%20not%20be%20making%20prophecies%20that%20have%20a%20major%20bearing%20on%20foreign%20policy%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20propriety%2C%20General%20Chauhan%20was%20voicing%20beliefs%20prevalent%20within%20domestic%20military%20circles%20regarding%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20declining%20power%20status%20and%20influence%2C%20following%20its%20ongoing%20catastrophic%20war%20with%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20consequent%20sanctions%20this%20had%20invited%20from%20the%20United%20States%20and%20its%20allies.%20Even%20though%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20vaunted%20military%20offensive%20has%20not%20altered%20the%20reality%20of%20Russian%20occupation%2C%20the%2020-month%20long%20war%20has%20effectively%20punctured%20the%20myth%20of%20Russian%20military%20indomitability%20and%20the%20competence%20of%20its%20varied%20platforms%20and%20equipment%20%E2%80%93%20a%20lot%20of%20which%20has%20proven%20operationally%20ineffective%20and%20inefficient%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20cross-section%20of%20serving%20and%20retired%20military%20officials%20privately%20doubted%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20maintain%20uninterrupted%20supplies%20of%20spares%2C%20components%20and%20sub-assemblies%20to%20India%20to%20sustain%20over%2065%25%20of%20in-service%20Russian%20equipment%2C%20and%20to%20deliver%20an%20assortment%20of%20platforms%20like%20air%20defence%20systems%2C%20frigates%2C%20a%20nuclear-powered%20attack%20submarine%20(SSN)%20and%20assault%20rifles%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20on%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%2C%20the%20services%20and%20officials%20in%20Moscow%20continue%20to%20put%20on%20a%20brave%20front%20by%20claiming%20that%20there%20are%20no%20hitches%20in%20bilateral%20military%20commerce%20between%20the%20two%20sides%2C%20problems%20endure%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20recently%20retired%20two-star%20Indian%20Army%20officer.%20These%20bottlenecks%20will%20continue%20to%20persist%2C%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20get%20worse%2C%20impinging%20negatively%20on%20our%20operational%20efficiency%2C%20he%20added%2C%20declining%20to%20be%20named%20given%20the%20sensitivity%20of%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20military%E2%80%99s%20dependency%20on%20Moscow%20continues%20to%20be%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bulk%20of%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%E2%80%99s%20(IAF)%2029-30%20fighter%20squadrons%20operate%20Russian%20platforms%20like%20260-odd%20multi-role%20%E2%80%98Flanker%E2%80%99%20Su-30MKIs%20fighters%2C%2084%20of%20which%20would%2C%20notably%2C%20be%20upgraded%20domestically%20to%20%E2%80%98Super%20Sukhoi%E2%80%99%20standards%20by%20fitting%20them%20with%205th%20generation%20features%20and%20rendering%20them%20capable%20of%20delivering%20a%20heavier%20weapons%20load.%20The%20IAF%20also%20employs%20some%2065%20retrofitted%20%E2%80%98Fulcrum%E2%80%99%20MiG-29UPG%20and%20around%2055-60%20%E2%80%98Fishbed%E2%80%99%20MiG%2021%20%E2%80%98Bis%E2%80%99%20ground%20attack%20combat%20aircraft%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20a%20large%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Russian%20military%20transports%2C%20mid-air%20refuellers%20and%20varied%20helicopters%2C%20all%20of%20which%20frequently%20need%20spares%2C%20without%20which%20they%20are%20simply%20inoperable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlongside%2C%20the%20Indian%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20(IN)%20principal%20warships%20are%20predominantly%20Russian%20in%20both%20origin%20and%20design.%20These%20include%20%3Cem%3EINS%20Vikramaditya%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(ex-%3Cem%3EAdmiral%20Gorshkov%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20the%20retrofitted%2044%2C500%20tonne%20Kiev-class%20aircraft%20carrier%20and%20its%20combat%20air%20arm%20of%2016%20MiG-29K%2FKuB%20fighters.%20The%20force%20also%20has%20another%2028%20MiG-29Ks%2C%20some%20of%20which%20are%20expected%20to%20temporarily%20comprise%20the%20combat%20fleet%20of%C2%A0the%20newly%20commissioned%20indigenous%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20%3Cem%3EINS%20Vikrant%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20IN%20also%20deploys%20an%20assortment%20of%20Kamov%20%E2%80%98Helix%E2%80%99%20Ka-28%20and%20Ka-31%20airborne%20early%20warning%20and%20control%20(AEW%26amp%3BC)%20rotary%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IN%E2%80%99s%20underwater%20platforms%20too%20included%20nine%20%E2%80%98Kilo%E2%80%99-class%20Type%20877%20diesel-electric%20submarines%20of%20a%20total%20of%2016%20such%20boats%2C%20while%20Russia%20had%20also%20provided%20the%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20(DRDO)%20assistance%20in%20designing%3Cem%3E%20INS%20Arihant%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20navy%E2%80%99s%20indigenously%20designed%20and%20built%20lead%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic%20missile%20submarine%20(SSBN)%20that%20joined%20service%20in%20August%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20also%20providing%20technical%20know-how%20to%20miniaturise%20the%2082.5MW%20reactor%20for%20the%204-5%20follow-on%20SSBN%E2%80%99s%20presently%20under%20construction%20at%20the%20classified%20Ship%20Building%20Centre%20at%20Visakhapatnam.%20No%20other%20country%20is%20willing%20to%20make%20such%20strategic%20technology%20transfers%20to%20India%2C%20but%20industry%20sources%20indicated%20that%20sanctions%20and%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20own%20needs%20could%20%E2%80%98thwart%E2%80%99%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20continue%20doing%20so%2C%20thereby%20imperilling%20the%20SSBN%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20over%2095%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20fleet%20of%20around%203%2C000%20main%20battle%20tanks%20(MBTs)%20operated%20by%2067-odd%20armoured%20regiments%20were%20Russian%20T-72%20and%20T-90S%20variants%20%E2%80%93%20imported%20directly%20and%20licence%20built%20%E2%80%93%20whilst%20some%202%2C000-odd%20infantry%20combat%20vehicles%20or%20ICVs%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Boyevaya%20Mashina%20Pekhoty%20(BMP)%201%20and%202%20%E2%80%93%20were%20similarly%20sourced.%20The%20latter%20were%20presently%20being%20upgraded%20with%20Russian%20assistance%2C%20which%2C%20too%2C%20could%20summarily%20end%20or%20be%20adversely%20impacted%20by%20the%20ongoing%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecurity%20officials%20are%20also%20concerned%20over%20the%20symbiosis%20that%20has%C2%A0emerged%20in%20recent%20months%20between%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20whose%20army%20has%20been%20locked%20in%20a%20standoff%20with%20the%20Indian%20Army%20in%20Ladakh%20since%20May%202020.%20They%20said%20this%20burgeoning%20association%20anticipated%20Russia%20gravitating%20swiftly%20towards%20cash-rich%20China%20for%20assistance%20to%20overcome%20sanctions%20and%20embargoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20association%20could%20end%20up%20being%20a%20simple%20trade-off%20between%20advanced%20Russian%20military%20knowhow%20in%20exchange%20for%20Chinese%20cash%20and%20vast%20industrial%20manufacturing%20capacity%20of%20assorted%20defence%20equipment%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20senior%20Navy%20veteran.%20Such%20an%20arrangement%20would%20be%20one%20of%20mutual%20advantage%20to%20both%20sides%20and%20one%20that%20could%20easily%20be%20reached%2C%20if%20it%20had%20not%20already%20been%20concluded%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20veterans%20were%20of%20the%20view%20that%20such%20inescapable%20sanctions%20%E2%80%93%20busting%20endeavours%20by%20Russia%20%E2%80%93%20could%2C%20as%20%E2%80%98payback%E2%80%99%2C%20result%20in%20China%20eventually%20pressuring%20Moscow%20to%20stanch%2C%20if%20not%20altogether%20cease%20the%20supply%20of%20assorted%20materiel%20and%20related%20equipment%20to%20India%20which%2C%20ironically%2C%20Delhi%20had%20acquired%20over%20decades%20to%20deter%20Beijing%20and%20its%20military%20and%20nuclear%20ally%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20reciprocal%20%E2%80%98no%20limits%E2%80%99%20friendship%20between%20Russia%20and%20China%20was%20on%20full%20display%20earlier%20this%20week%20in%20Beijing%2C%20where%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-67143322%5C%22%3Ehosted%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20130-nation%20jamboree%20to%20celebrate%20his%20signature%20decade-old%20global%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI).%20The%20BRI%20essentially%20envisages%20China%20investing%20in%20over%20150%20countries%20and%20international%20organisations%20to%20further%20its%20global%20strategic%20and%20financial%20influence%20to%20counter%20that%20of%20the%20US%20and%20the%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPutin%2C%20who%20has%20rarely%20left%20Russia%20after%20invading%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%2C%20was%20the%20guest%20of%20honour%20at%20the%20meet.%20Speaking%20immediately%20after%20Xi%2C%20he%20pledged%20support%20to%20China%20and%20its%20BRI%20project%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cin%20tune%20with%20Russian%20ideas%E2%80%9D%20and%20heaped%20lavish%20praise%20on%20Beijing%20for%20its%20achievements%20since%20the%20initiatives%20launched%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Beijing-Moscow%20axis%20that%20has%20been%20proliferating%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20is%20now%20poised%20to%20become%20firmer%2C%20posing%20a%20formidable%20threat%20to%20world%20peace%2C%20as%20both%20strive%20to%20aggressively%20carve%20out%20a%20new%20regional%20and%20global%20order%20based%20arbitrarily%20on%20financial%20and%20military%20might%20and%20the%20recent%20Israel-Gaza%20crisis%20had%20only%20worsened%20the%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Brigadier%20Rahul%20Bhonsle%20of%20the%20Security%20Risks%20consultancy%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20India%2C%20which%20had%20incrementally%20emerged%20as%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20proxy%20over%20the%20past%2015%20years%20to%20manage%20China%2C%20could%20well%20end%20up%20facing%20the%20brunt%20of%20this%20deadly%20security%20partnership%20between%20Moscow%2C%20Beijing%20and%20Islamabad%2C%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20veterans%20say%20General%20Chauhan%E2%80%99s%20forecast%20regarding%20Russia%20needs%20attention%2C%20it%20also%20presents%20the%20CDS%20and%20the%20three%20services%20with%20a%20further%20dilemma%20that%20somewhat%20bedevils%20easy%20resolution.%20And%20though%20defence%20diplomacy%20is%20part%20of%20the%20CDS%E2%80%99s%20overarching%20charter%2C%20making%20public%20statements%2C%20even%20if%20apposite%20and%20accurate%2C%20tend%20to%20constrict%20India%E2%80%99s%20diplomatic%20elbow%20room%20in%20the%20prevailing%20geopolitical%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOr%2C%20as%20the%20French%20statesman%20Georges%20Clemenceau%20memorably%20declared%3A%20%E2%80%98War%20is%20too%20serious%20a%20business%20to%20be%20left%20to%20the%20generals.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697804131000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20153016%2Fimage-1417.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fcdss-undiplomatic-talk-of-russian-decline-turns-focus-on-weapon-procurement-challenges-india-may-face%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delivering%20the%2014th%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20L.M.%20Katrememorial%20lecture%20in%20Bengaluru%20last%20weekend%2C%20General%20Chauhan%20declared%20that%20the%20geopolitical%20importance%20of%20Russia%20would%20decline%20in%20times%20to%20come%2C%20despite%20it%20being%20a%20nuclear%20power.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fcdss-undiplomatic-talk-of-russian-decline-turns-focus-on-weapon-procurement-challenges-india-may-face%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20How%20Russia%2C%20China%20Found%20Common%20Cause%20In%20Israel-Hamas%20War%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWith%20anger%20building%20across%20the%20Middle%20East%20over%20Israel's%20strikes%20in%20Gaza%2C%20China%20and%20Russia%20are%20finding%20common%20cause%20with%20countries%20across%20the%20region%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Moscow%20and%20Beijing%2C%20Israel's%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza%20following%20the%20Hamas%20attacks%20that%20killed%201%2C400%20Israelis%20presents%20an%20opportunity%20to%20burnish%20their%20credentials%20as%20the%20champions%20of%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20in%20contrast%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20which%20has%20put%20its%20support%20squarely%20behind%20ally%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20consistently%20called%20for%20restraint%20and%20a%20ceasefire%20but%20has%20also%20sharpened%20its%20criticism%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsrael's%20actions%20have%20gone%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20self-defence%2C%26quot%3B%20Chinese%20Foreign%20Minister%20Wang%20Yi%20said%20this%20week%2C%20calling%20on%20it%20to%20stop%20its%20%26quot%3Bcollective%20punishment%26quot%3B%20of%20Gaza%20residents%2C%20Chinese%20state%20media%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20expressed%20sympathy%20for%20the%20Palestinians%20while%20blaming%20the%20US%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20many%20people%20will%20agree%20with%20me%20that%20this%20is%20a%20vivid%20example%20of%20the%20failure%20of%20United%20States%20policy%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%26quot%3B%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20said%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20Putin%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20have%20sought%20to%20deepen%20ties%20to%20the%20global%20south%2C%20seeing%20economic%20opportunities%20and%20possibly%20a%20way%20to%20counterbalance%20the%20diplomatic%20influence%20of%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20on%20display%20this%20week%20as%20China%20hosted%20a%20summit%20for%20Xi's%20signature%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%2C%20which%20has%20lent%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20for%20infrastructure%20projects%20across%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Africa%2C%20Latin%20America%20and%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPutin%20attended%20and%20met%20Xi%20for%20three%20hours%20of%20talks%20that%20included%20%26quot%3Ban%20in-depth%20exchange%20of%20views%20on%20the%20Palestinian-Israeli%20situation%26quot%3B%2C%20China%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20and%20Russia%20still%20see%20(the%20crisis)%20more%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20United%20States%20than%20in%20terms%20of%20either%20Palestine%20or%20Israel%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jon%20Alterman%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20Program%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20United%20States%20can%20effectively%20rally%20the%20world%2C%20it's%20bad%20for%20them.%20If%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20grow%20increasingly%20isolated%2C%20they%20see%20that%20as%20good%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupport%20For%20Palestine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20strategies%20of%20Russia%20and%20China%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20are%20not%20fu