e%20country%20and%20demanded%20that%20the%20platforms%20maintain%20neutrality%20in%20the%20upcoming%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20letters%20came%20after%20the%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20a%20series%20of%20reports%20which%20claimed%20that%20Facebook%2C%20WhatsApp%2C%20and%20YouTube%20had%20failed%20to%20control%20communal%20and%20Hindutva%20content%2C%20often%20generated%20by%20those%20associated%20%E2%80%93%20either%20directly%20or%20loosely%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECiting%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPost%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20report%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F09%2F26%2Findia-monu-manesar-viligante-social-media%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20live-streamed%20his%20attacks%20on%20Indian%20Muslims.%20YouTube%20gave%20him%20an%20award%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20about%20the%20role%20of%20YouTube%20in%20%E2%80%9Cpropagating%20communal%20hatred%20and%20dividing%20the%20country%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20letter%20to%20Pichai%20said%20that%20Google%20and%20specifically%20YouTube%20is%20culpable%20of%20abetting%20social%20disharmony%20and%20inciting%20communal%20hatred%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%20we%20have%20data%20that%20shows%20algorithmic%20moderation%20and%20suppression%20of%20opposition%20leaders%E2%80%99%20content%20on%20your%20platform%20while%20also%20promoting%20ruling%20party%20content%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20blatant%20partisanship%20and%20bias%20towards%20one%20political%20formation%20by%20a%20private%20foreign%20company%20is%20tantamount%20to%20interfering%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%2C%20one%20that%20we%20in%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20cannot%20but%20take%20seriously.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKarnataka%20minister%20and%20Congress%20leader%20Priyank%20Kharge%20also%20accused%20YouTube%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpreventing%20users%20from%20engaging%20with%20democratic%20voices.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EHello%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FYouTubeIndia%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40YouTubeIndia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGoogleIndia%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40GoogleIndia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20quite%20intriguing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20categorized%20the%20public%20speeches%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRahulGandhi%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40RahulGandhi%3C%2Fa%3E%20ji%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fpriyankagandhi%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40priyankagandhi%3C%2Fa%3E%20ji%20as%20related%20to%20self-harm%20and%20suicide.%20Are%20you%20actively%20discouraging%2C%20dissuading%20and%20preventing%20viewers%20from%20engaging%20with%20democratic%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FPPJsA6Qys8%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FPPJsA6Qys8%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Priyank%20Kharge%20%2F%20%E0%B2%AA%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%B0%E0%B2%BF%E0%B2%AF%E0%B2%BE%E0%B2%82%E0%B2%95%E0%B3%8D%20%E0%B2%96%E0%B2%B0%E0%B3%8D%E0%B2%97%E0%B3%86%20(%40PriyankKharge)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPriyankKharge%2Fstatus%2F1715053462927601758%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2019%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20are%20succumbing%20to%20pressure%20from%20the%20Central%20Government%20in%20making%20these%20decisions%2C%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20the%20State%20Government%20is%20equally%20adept%20at%20this%20kind%20of%20maneuvering%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%20on%20X%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFurthermore%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20eagerly%20waiting%20to%20listen%20and%20learn%20from%20you%20about%20the%20categorization%20of%20a%20LIVE%20RALLY%20as%20self-harming%20or%20suicidal%2C%20even%20before%20the%20speakers%20have%20spoken%20a%20single%20word.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYouTube%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fyoutube%2Fanswer%2F2802245%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epolicy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20states%20that%20it%20does%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20allow%20content%20on%20YouTube%20that%20promotes%20suicide%2C%20self-harm%2C%20or%20eating%20disorders%2C%20that%20is%20intended%20to%20shock%20or%20disgust%2C%20or%20that%20poses%20a%20considerable%20risk%20to%20viewers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20her%20speech%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20had%20referred%20to%20a%20woman%20who%20died%20by%20suicide%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20situation%20in%20the%20state%20is%20such%20that%2040%20lakh%20youth%20are%20unemployed.%20BRS%20promised%20to%20give%20jobs%20to%20every%20family.%20Today%20lakhs%20of%20posts%20are%20lying%20vacant%20but%20jobs%20have%20not%20been%20given.%20Such%20is%20the%20situation%20that%20there%20is%20corruption%20even%20in%20the%20application%20process.%20A%20young%20girl%20killed%20herself%20and%20even%20on%20her%20questions%20were%20raised%20that%20she%20had%20not%20filled%20the%20application%20form.%20Instead%20of%20understanding%20the%20youth%E2%80%99s%20problems%20fingers%20are%20pointed%20at%20them%20but%20their%20problems%20are%20not%20solved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20BJP%20on%20Friday%20has%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20accusations%20and%20asked%20the%20party%20%E2%80%9Cto%20look%20within.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20X%2C%20BJP%20IT%20cell%20chief%20Amit%20Malviya%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Famitmalviya%2Fstatus%2F1715274465599172631%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9D%20bad%20craftsman%20always%20blames%20his%20tools%20for%20poor%20outcome.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697796044000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19181855%2Fimage-1410.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fyoutube-warning-tags-rahul-priyanka-congress-criticism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20social%20media%20platform%20added%20%E2%80%9Cself%20harm%E2%80%9D%20tags%20to%20a%20video%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra's%20speeches%20in%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20Mulugu%20on%20October%2018.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fyoutube-warning-tags-rahul-priyanka-congress-criticism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%20Govt%20Order%20Banning%20Sharing%20of%20Media%20Related%20to%20Violence%20Potentially%20Unconstitutional%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30163218%2FFwqAt6VXsAIGp1_.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Manipur%20Home%20Department%20notified%20Order%20No.%20H-3608%2F2%2F2023-HD-HD%C2%A0%20on%20October%2011%2C%202023%20%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-photo-video-footage-ban%5C%22%3Erestrains%20the%20sharing%20of%20videos%2Fimages%20depicting%20acts%20of%20violence%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20(IFF)%20believes%20this%20order%20infringes%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20limits%20journalistic%20freedom%20and%20hampers%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20essential%20information.%20We%20wrote%20to%20the%20Manipur%20Home%20Department%20to%20reconsider%20these%20restrictions%2C%20citing%20constitutional%20violations%20and%20potential%20dangers%20to%20citizens%E2%80%99%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Should%20You%20Care%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EManipur%20has%20been%20under%20an%20information%20blockade%20since%20May%202023.%20This%20order%20strengthens%20the%20blockade%20by%20severely%20restricting%20the%20essential%20journalistic%20freedoms%20of%20media%20and%20news%20professionals%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20of%20all%20residents%20of%20Manipur.%20Further%2C%20the%20circulation%20of%20information%20via%20visual%20media%20equips%20people%20to%20assess%20their%20immediate%20surroundings%20better%20and%20travel%20safely%20in%20their%20vicinity%20for%20access%20to%20resources.%20This%20order%20virtually%20impedes%20the%20capacity%20of%20a%20person%20to%20receive%20information%20pertaining%20to%20the%20violence%20taking%20place%20in%20their%20vicinity%2C%20and%20thereby%20places%20them%20in%20potential%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmidst%20the%20ongoing%20internet%20blackout%2C%20there%20comes%20a%20new%20restriction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOwing%20to%20the%20ongoing%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20between%20communities%2C%20the%20state%20has%20been%20subjected%20to%20multiple%20internet%20shutdowns%20in%20the%20year%202023.%20The%20first%20shutdown%20was%20imposed%20on%20May%203%2C%202023%2C%20and%20the%20latest%20internet%20shutdown%20order%20was%20issued%20on%20October%201%2C%202023%2C%20which%20is%20still%20ongoing.%20Amidst%20the%20communication%20challenges%20already%20existing%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20blackout%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20Manipur%20decided%20to%20issue%20yet%20another%20order%20that%20explicitly%20bars%20the%20sharing%20of%20videos%2Fimages%20portraying%20violent%20incidents%20in%20the%20state%20which%20aims%20to%20curb%20violence.%20IFF%20argues%20that%20this%20order%20oversteps%20constitutional%20boundaries%20and%20jeopardises%20essential%20freedoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20prohibits%20the%20circulation%20of%20any%20images%2Fvideos%20that%20depict%20violent%20activities%2C%20such%20as%20causing%20injury%20to%20the%20body%20and%2For%20damaging%20public%20or%20private%20property%2C%20via%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20explicitly%20mentioning%20WhatsApp%2C%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20Twitter%2C%20etc.%20Though%20the%20stated%20intention%20of%20this%20order%20is%20to%20bring%20%E2%80%9Cnormalcy%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20State%2C%20the%20order%20states%20that%20the%20circulation%20of%20the%20above%20via%20electronic%20equipment%20like%20mobile%20phones%2C%20computers%2C%20tablets%20etc.%20or%20even%20the%20possession%20of%20such%20material%20will%20result%20in%20%E2%80%9Cappropriate%20legal%20action%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20mandates%20that%20the%20violation%20of%20its%20provisions%20will%20result%20in%20the%20person%20being%20%E2%80%9Cbooked%20and%20prosecuted%E2%80%9D%3B%20thereby%20severely%20limiting%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20by%20way%20of%20not%20making%20other%20citizens%20aware%20of%20a%20potentially%20hostile%20environment%2C%20directly%20contravening%20the%20right%20to%20life%20by%20putting%20the%20people%20in%20harm%E2%80%99s%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20order%20is%20potentially%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20Manipur%20(Home)%20enlisting%20our%20concerns%20and%20the%20impact%20it%20could%20have%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20rights%20and%20digital%20liberties.%20We%20highlighted%20the%20following%2C%20among%20other%2C%20concerns%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuppression%20of%20Legitimate%20Journalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20This%20measure%20could%20significantly%20suppress%20legitimate%20journalism.%20By%20restricting%20the%20dissemination%20of%20information%2C%20it%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20severely%20limit%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20pertinent%20news%20and%20crucial%20insights.%20Consequently%2C%20it%20could%20hinder%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20gain%20a%20comprehensive%20understanding%20of%20the%20current%20situation%20and%20make%20informed%20decisions.%20Moreover%2C%20this%20restriction%20could%20have%20broader%20implications%20for%20communal%20violence%20investigations%2C%20where%20the%20availability%20of%20crucial%20evidence%20may%20be%20stifled%20due%20to%20limited%20investigative%20resources.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EViolation%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Free%20Speech%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Beyond%20its%20effect%20on%20journalism%2C%20this%20measure%20has%20serious%20implications%20for%20free%20speech.%20It%20imposes%20prior%20restraint%20by%20engaging%20in%20pre-censorship%20and%20effectively%20prohibiting%20the%20sharing%20of%20videos%20or%20images%20before%20these%20events%20transpire.%20This%20act%20contradicts%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20which%20safeguards%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression.%20This%20was%20affirmed%20by%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Brij%20Bhushan%20vs%20The%20State%20Of%20Delhi%2C%20which%20found%20that%20prior%20restraint%20on%20speech%20based%20on%20presumption%20is%20fundamentally%20unconstitutional.%20Furthermore%2C%20this%20measure%20stifles%20the%20marketplace%20of%20ideas%2C%20as%20limiting%20discourse%20can%20undermine%20the%20very%20foundations%20of%20a%20democratic%20society.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EOverbreadth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20measure%E2%80%99s%20overbroad%20language%20adds%20another%20layer%20of%20concern.%20It%20prohibits%20the%20sharing%20of%20media%20content%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20may%20aggravate%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20in%20the%20State.%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20notably%20vague%20and%2C%20when%20scrutinised%2C%20does%20not%20fall%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20specific%20legal%20provisions%20under%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20or%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act.%20Further%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3EShreya%20Singhal%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20rectified%20a%20pre-existing%20provision%20that%20was%20overbroad%20and%20impermissibly%20restricted%20free%20speech%2C%20aligning%20it%20more%20closely%20with%20constitutional%20standards.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EViolation%20of%20Article%2021%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Finally%2C%20the%20measure%20is%20violative%20of%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%20The%20punitive%20consequences%20listed%20in%20this%20measure%20serve%20as%20a%20deterrent%20for%20the%20public%20to%20share%20information%20and%20be%20aware%2C%20consequently%20compromising%20their%20ability%20to%20protect%20their%20own%20lives.%20The%20sharing%20of%20media%20content%20mentioned%20in%20the%20order%20can%20be%20vital%20for%20the%20citizens%20of%20Manipur%20to%20exercise%20vigilance%20in%20terms%20of%20location%2C%20time%2C%20and%20the%20general%20ambience%20of%20areas%2C%20thus%20enabling%20them%20to%20safeguard%20themselves.%20In%20essence%2C%20this%20measure%20not%20only%20hinders%20access%20to%20information%20but%20also%20endangers%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20citizens%20of%20Manipur.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20concern%20over%20the%20Manipur%20government%E2%80%99s%20recent%20order%20reflects%20a%20broader%20debate%20on%20balancing%20security%20measures%20with%20citizens%E2%80%99%20constitutional%20rights.%20As%20digital%20rights%20become%20increasingly%20vital%20in%20our%20society%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20navigate%20these%20complexities%20with%20careful%20consideration%20for%20individual%20freedoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20advocated%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20residents%20of%20Manipur%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20internet%20shutdowns%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fmanipur-online-censorship%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2F%5C%22%3EInternet%20Freedom%20Foundation.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697796033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30163218%2FFwqAt6VXsAIGp1_.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmanipur-govt-order-banning-sharing-of-media-related-to-violence-potentially-unconstitutional%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20has%20argued%20that%20this%20order%20oversteps%20constitutional%20boundaries%20and%20jeopardises%20essential%20freedoms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmanipur-govt-order-banning-sharing-of-media-related-to-violence-potentially-unconstitutional%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20soldier%20who%20fled%20to%20North%20Korea%20hit%20with%20child%20abuse%20image%20and%20desertion%20charges%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697795820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F768x432%2Fskynews-travis-king-north-korea_6224049.jpg%3F20231020111856%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftravis-king-us-soldier-who-fled-to-north-korea-hit-with-child-abuse-image-and-desertion-charges-12988269%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Travis%20King%2C%20the%20US%20soldier%20who%20fled%20to%20North%20Korea%2C%20has%20been%20charged%20with%20desertion%20and%20the%20solicitation%20of%20indecent%20images%20of%20children.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A74%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftravis-king-us-soldier-who-fled-to-north-korea-hit-with-child-abuse-image-and-desertion-charges-12988269%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%